Sentencas: This paper describes the structure and electrochemical properties of solid oxide fuel cell cathodes prepared by infiltration of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-(delta) (LSCF) into porous Gd-Doped Ceria (GDC).
Titulo: Solid oxide fuel cell cathodes by infiltration of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ into Gd-Doped Ceria

Sentencas: The CDC scaffolds were prepared by partial sintering of GDC compacts on dense CDC electrolytes.
Titulo: Solid oxide fuel cell cathodes by infiltration of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ into Gd-Doped Ceria

Sentencas: LSCF was introduced into these structures by multiple infiltrations of aqueous nitrate solutions followed by firing.
Titulo: Solid oxide fuel cell cathodes by infiltration of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ into Gd-Doped Ceria

Sentencas: The cathode polarization resistance, measured using electrochemical impedance spectroscopy on symmetrical cells, showed a pronounced minimum as a function of CDC firing temperature at 1100-1200 degrees C, where the microstructure was well-necked but porous with similar to 300-nm-sized particles.
Titulo: Solid oxide fuel cell cathodes by infiltration of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ into Gd-Doped Ceria

Sentencas: Increasing the infiltrated LSCF loading decreased the polarization resistance up to the highest loading tested, 12.5 vol.%.
Titulo: Solid oxide fuel cell cathodes by infiltration of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ into Gd-Doped Ceria

Sentencas: Decreasing the LSCF firing temperature decreased the polarization resistance due to a decrease in the LSCF feature size from similar to 1 mu m at 1200 degrees C to similar to 50 nm at 800 degrees C. Thus, the infiltration method allowed separate control over the nnicrostructures of the CDC and LSCF phases.
Titulo: Solid oxide fuel cell cathodes by infiltration of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ into Gd-Doped Ceria

Sentencas: The lowest polarization resistance measured at 600 degrees C was 0.24 Omega cm(2).
Titulo: Solid oxide fuel cell cathodes by infiltration of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ into Gd-Doped Ceria
